[[!meta title="How to rotate a video"]]

Make sure you have:

	deb http://www.debian-multimedia.org unstable main

in your `sources.list`. Then `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install mencoder`.

Finally, run something like:

	mencoder -vf rotate=1 -o rotated.avi -oac copy -ovc lavc /mnt/sd/dcim/101canon/mvi_3099.avi

* [Further scaling tips](http://therning.org/niklas/2006/07/rotating-video-clips-shot-in-portrait-mode/)

If you take the video from upside down:

	mencoder -vf mirror,flip -o flip-mirror.avi -oac copy -ovc lavc /mnt/sd/dcim/101canon/mvi_3104.avi
